         <abstract>
            <p>An upper bound of the norm of the error vector after n time steps is 1/2(n + 1) (n + 2) |δ&lt;sup&gt;*&lt;/sup&gt;|. For the explicit scheme δ&lt;sup&gt;*&lt;/sup&gt; = |δ&lt;sup&gt;*&lt;/sup&gt;| = 3 × 1/2 × 10&lt;sup&gt;-p&lt;/sup&gt; where p is the number of decimals carried in the computations. For the implicit scheme δ&lt;sup&gt;*&lt;/sup&gt; = | δ&lt;sup&gt;*&lt;/sup&gt;| is an upper bound of the errors which arise both from using approximations to A&lt;sup&gt;-1&lt;/sup&gt; and A&lt;sup&gt;-1&lt;/sup&gt;B in the determination of u&lt;sub&gt;k+1&lt;/sub&gt; from equation (6&lt;sup&gt;*&lt;/sup&gt;) and from rounding off the values of the products and quotients involved in the computation of the components of u&lt;sub&gt;k+1&lt;/sub&gt;.</p>
